📜 Random Indian Quotes Generator

A simple React project that displays random Indian quotes with the click of a button.
This project is great for learning the basics of React.js, state management, and component styling.

🚀 Features

Displays a random quote from India each time you click the button.

Contains 50+ unique quotes from Indian leaders, philosophers, and thinkers.

Responsive design (works on desktop and mobile).

Built with React + Tailwind CSS for clean UI.

🖼️ Demo

👉 (You can deploy this project to Netlify or Vercel, then add your live demo link here)

🛠️ Tech Stack

React.js (Frontend library)

Tailwind CSS (Styling)

JavaScript (ES6+)

📂 Project Structure
random-quotes/
├── public/
├── src/
│   ├── components/
│   │   └── QuoteBox.js
│   ├── App.js
│   ├── index.js
│   └── quotes.js   // contains the 50 Indian quotes
├── package.json
└── README.md

⚡ Getting Started
1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/your-username/random-indian-quotes.git
cd random-indian-quotes

2. Install dependencies
npm install

3. Run the development server
npm start


Now open http://localhost:3000
 in your browser.

📖 Usage

Click “Get Quote” button → shows a new random quote.

Quotes come from a predefined list of 50+ Indian quotes.

Great for practice and learning React basics.

